          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "My kid is studying in Grade III. I am happy to join my kid in SNS family. He joined for Grade 2 and initially I was scared how he could perform because he studied in a school were there few kids. Thanks to SNS family and now my son has grew up as a confident speaker. The school has provided him the many opportunities through competitions and good motivation from management , staffs and even co workers. I am very happy and glad that I choose correct platform. He participated in ALL ROUNDER PERFOEMER (  ARP) award competition for the first time in his grade 2, n he got award from technical director Nalin sir.I am very happy  and which motivated him to join again in Grade 3 , he got through two rounds.The second round  as poster presentation gave a better platform to improve presentation skills,  my kid spoke very confidently. GOOD IN EXTRACURRICULAR ACTIVITES LIKE SWIMMING, SPORTS.\n\nTHANKS TO SNS FAMILY FOR INTRODUCING THE KIDS TO ENTREPRENEURSHIP\nWORLD AND DESIGN THINKING AT THE EARLIER STAGE.\nMY SON RITHVIK KRISHNA CURRENTLY IN GRADE III B  WANTS TO CONTINUE HIS STUDIES ONLY IN SNS FAMILY.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "SNS Academy - Fathima Nagar"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Sow Karthika"
          },
          "datePublished": "2024-12-16",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "4",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I am delighted to have enrolled my child in SNS Academy. The teachers are kind, and their calm and thoughtful approach to engaging with the children is truly commendable. The school’s infrastructure and the events they organize, such as Family Day, Grandparents’ Day, ramp walks, and various celebrations, bring immense joy while fostering learning and growth. Witnessing my 3.5-year-old confidently walk on stage without fear was a remarkable moment. My heartfelt thanks to the school and its management for creating such a nurturing and empowering environment.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
